CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 6, reads: "The Jums - Members of the Just Us Mothers Club, known as the JUMs were never more beautiful than they were last Friday night when they celebrated their 15th anniversary at a formal ball held at the Hotel Roosevelt. Left to right, first row: Mmes. Marcy [Mary] Jane Page, social chairman; Marjorie Coy, Viola Woods, Elena Chapman, president; Addie Trent, Alberta Atwater and Ann Barnett.  Last row: Mmes. Mary Barnett, Louise Smith, Gwendolyn Bates, Louise Clark, Mildred Woods, Ardelle Douglass, Betty Fowler, Jessie Anderson, Elva Robinson and Geraldyne Mike. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of JUMS (Just Us Mothers) Club members, first row from left: Mary Jane Page, Marjorie Coy, Viola Woods, Elena Chapman, Addie Trent, Alberta Atwater, Ann Barnett; second row: Mary Barnett, Louise Smith, Gwendolyn Bates, Louise Clark, Mildred Woods, Ardelle Douglass, Betty Fowler, Jessie Anderson, Elva Robinson, and Geraldyne Mike, gathered in Roosevelt Hotel for fifteenth anniversary ball
